name: Jefferson Building
directions: Large, open bathroom in the Gender, Women, Sexuality department and possibly on the other floors as well.
comment: I've gone many times and have never been harassed. It is mostly professor's offices, which can seem intimidating, but people generally aren't paying attention to other people.

name: T Spoons
directions: In the back
comment: You need a key from the employees to get in

name: Canadore College West Nipissing Campus
directions: If you enter from the door under the MX Construction sign, it's up the stairs and left until you can go downstairs, on the left wall. Not positive about how to reach it from the Canadore College entrance.
comment: It's technically a college building but it has several organizations and companies in it (like A1 Driving School and MX Construction), so just look like you know where you're going. There's parking on the other side of the building, too.

name: Sugar Land Marriott Town Square
directions: On the ground floor of the hotel, they have gendered (male and female) bathrooms with stalls and one separate unisex/disabled bathroom - with lock.

name: Great Falls Visitor Center
directions: Between the parking lot and the visitor's center there are restrooms. Between the gendered restrooms there is a family restroom
comment: There is an admission fee to get into the park during the day but in the late evening it seems to be free - I always go after work and there is never anyone to take admission.

comment: It's at the Subway across from Ohio State University's Ohio Union

directions: If you're back by the theaters, there's a hallway on the right. It's at the end. It's across from theater 8.

name: Rendezvous Hair Salon

comment: They are really chill there. They'd probably let someone use it even without getting a haircut.

name: Stone Tavern
comment: They're single stalls and have functioning locks but it's still a bar, so use caution.

name: Scribbles Coffee
directions: In the back room, on the left.
comment: You should probably buy a coffee but if you're broke they also sell books so you can say you're looking for a book.

comment: Have to show a valid student ID after normal hours to get in the library.

Friendly area, good food too ;-). 

Probably able to use washroom if you asked nicely if you don't want to buy anything.
